Overview

This project focuses on creating and auditing ethical AI systems, detecting and mitigating bias, and promoting responsible deployment.

Parts & Deliverables

Part 1: Theoretical Understanding (30%)

Defined algorithmic bias with examples.

Explained transparency vs explainability.

GDPR impact on AI in the EU.

Matched ethical principles: Justice, Non-maleficence, Autonomy, Sustainability.
Deliverable: PDF

Part 2: Case Study Analysis (40%)

Biased Hiring Tool: Identified bias, proposed fixes, suggested fairness metrics.

Facial Recognition in Policing: Discussed ethical risks, recommended responsible policies.
Deliverable: PDF

Part 3: Practical Fairness Audit (25%)

Dataset: COMPAS recidivism

Tools: Python, Pandas, Matplotlib, AI Fairness 360

Steps: Cleaned data, binarized labels, mapped race, applied Reweighing, computed fairness metrics, visualized results.
Deliverable: Jupyter Notebook / Python script

Part 4: Ethical Reflection (5%)

Personal project reflection: fairness, transparency, privacy, monitoring, and human oversight.
Deliverable: Short PDF section